tion":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"noun","gloss":"sinning, committing adultery"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to act immorally, to be wicked, to sin","examples":[{"text":"بَلْ يُرِيدُ الْإِنْسَانُ لِيَفْجُرَ أَمَامَهُ","english":"but man desires to act sinfully in what is before him"}]},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to cleave, to break up, to dig up"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to create an outlet or passage (for water)"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to let pour forth","examples":[{"text":"إِذَا السَّمَاء ٱنْفَطَرَتْ ۝ وَإِذَا ٱلْكَوَاكِبُ ٱنْتَثَرَتْ ۝ وَإِذَا ٱلْبِحَارُ فُجِّرَتْ ۝ وَإِذَا ٱلْقُبُورُ بُعْثِرَتْ ۝ عَلِمَتْ نَفْسٌ مَّا قَدَّمَتْ وَأَخَّرَتْ ۝","english":"When the sky breaks apart / And when the stars commence to scatter / And when the seas gush forth / And when the graves are strewn / A soul will know what it has put forward and what it has set back."}]},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to cleave, to split"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to explode"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"verbal noun of فَجَرَ (fajara, “to break up, to sin”) (form I)","tags":["form-of","noun-from-verb"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"dawn, daybreak; dayspring","examples":[{"text":"فِي الْفَجْرِ الْبَاكِرِ، كَانَتِ الشُّوَارِعُ هَادِئَةً وَخَالِيَةً مِنَ الزُّحَامِ.","english":"In the early dawn, the streets were quiet and free from traffic."},{"text":"سَلَامٌ هِيَ حَتَّى مَطْلَعِ الْفَجْرِ","english":"Abdulala Maududi: All peace is that night until the rise of dawn."}]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"dawn, beginning, outset, start","tags":["figuratively"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"اَلْفَجْر (al-fajr): ellipsis of صَلَاة الْفَجْر (ṣalāt al-fajr, “dawn prayer”)","tags":["definite"],"examples":[{"text":"صَلَّيْنَا الْفَجْرَ جَمَاعَةً","english":"we pray the dawn prayer in congregration"}]},{"pos":"name","gloss":"a female given name"}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"From Proto-Semitic *pagr- (“body, trunk”). Cognate with Akkadian 𒇿 (pagrum, “body, trunk, torso, corpse, carcass”), Hebrew פֶּגֶר (péger, “corpse, carcass”), Classical Syriac ܦܲܓܪܵܐ (paḡrā), and Classical Mandaic ࡐࡀࡂࡓࡀ (pāġrā)."},"ipa":["/fad͡ʒr/","/fa.d͡ʒa.ra/","/fad͡ʒ.d͡ʒa.ra/"]}